pages.general_notes_verbatim:
CONCRETE MASONRY WALL ANCHORAGE NOTES
1. CONCRETE MASONRY UNITS SHALL CONFORM TO ASTM C90 WITH 2,000 PSI COMPRESSIVE STRENGTH TO ASTM C744.
2. A MAXIMUM OF ONE ANCHOR IS PERMITTED TO BE INSTALLED IN EACH UNIT CELL.
3. EMBEDMENT IS MEASURED FROM OUTSIDE SURFACE OF CMU TO THE EMBEDDED END OF THE ANCHOR.
4. ADJACENT ANCHORS MUST BE NO LESS THAN 4" APART. ANCHORS MUST BE INSTALLED A MINIMUM OF 12" FROM THE EDGE OF THE MASONRY WALL TO THE CENTRE OF THE ANCHOR

ABBREVIATIONS
AB - ANCHOR BOLTS
BP - BASEPLATE
C/W - CONNECTED WITH
DIA. Ø(Ø) = DIAMETER
EL - ELEVATION
ELEV. = EACH WAY
GR - GUARDRAIL
HR - HANDRAIL
ID. = INNER DIAMETER
IL - INNER DIAMETER
MIN. = MINIMUM
MAX. = MAXIMUM
O.C. = ON CENTRE
PL = POINT LOAD
THK = THICKNESS
T.O.C. = TOP OF CONCRETE
TYP. = TYPICAL
UNO = UNLESS NOTED OTHERWISE

GENERAL NOTES
1. DESIGN AND CONSTRUCTION OF ALL WORK ON THIS PROJECT SHALL CONFORM TO LATEST EDITIONS OF THE FOLLOWING:
- NATIONAL BUILDING CODE
- ONTARIO BUILDING CODE
- LOCAL REGULATIONS
- OSHA REGULATIONS
- CWA GENERAL SPECIFICATION FOR THE DESIGN AND ENGINEERING OF ARTIFICIAL CLIMBING STRUCTURES.
2. DRAWINGS ARE NOT TO BE SCALED.
3. THE CONTRACTOR SHALL CHECK AND VERIFY ALL SITE CONDITIONS AND MEASUREMENTS AND REPORT ANY DISCREPANCIES TO THE ENGINEER.
4. NO CHANGES SHALL BE MADE WITHOUT THE ENGINEER'S APPROVAL.
5. CONTRACTOR SHALL MAKE ADEQUATE PROVISIONS FOR TEMPORARY BRACING AND SHORING. CONSTRUCTION LOADS SHALL NOT EXCEED THE DESIGN LOADS NOTED ON DRAWINGS.

STEEL NOTES
1. ALL DIMENSIONS ARE IN INCHES UNLESS NOTED OTHERWISE.
2. ALL HOLE SIZES ARE 9/16" DIAMETER UNLESS OTHERWISE NOTED.
3. ALL BOLTS SHALL BE 1/2" DIAMETER A325 STRUCTURAL BOLTS UNLESS OTHERWISE NOTED.
4. WHERE NO WELD SYMBOL IS SHOWN, ASSUME FILLET ALL AROUND, WITH SIZE EQUAL TO THE LESSER OF 3/16" OR THE MINIMUM THICKNESS OF ADJOINING STRUCTURAL STEEL.
5. STRUCTURAL STEEL PLATES, ANGLES, AND CHANNELS SHALL CONFORM TO CSA G40.20/.21-350W.
6. WELDING SHALL CONFORM TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF CSA STANDARD W59 AND SHAL...
pages.page_overview_summary: This sheet provides comprehensive general notes for the design and construction of a modular panel climbing wall and ECO frames. It includes specifications for concrete masonry wall anchorage, steel components, and climbing wall design loads. The notes emphasize compliance with national and local building codes, and detail the responsibilities of the contractor and owner. Important load factors and seismic considerations for the Brampton, ON location are also included.
